{"sectionId":636,"sectionIdLiteral":"636","humanId":"lesson-224","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"God is my Father, and He loves His Son.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 224"},"annotation":"W-224","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-224\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"636#1\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"636#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>My true Identity is so secure, so lofty, sinless, glorious and great, wholly beneficent and free from guilt, that Heaven looks to It to give it light.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"636#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>It lights the world as well.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"636#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>It is the gift my Father gave to me; the one as well I give the world.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"636#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>There is no gift but this that can be either given or received.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"636#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>This is reality, and only this.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"636#1:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>This is illusion‚Äôs end.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"636#1:7\"><span class=\"snr\">7</span>It is the truth.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"636#2\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"636#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>My Name, O Father, still is known to You.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"636#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>I have forgotten It, and do not know where I am going, who I am, or what it is I do.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"636#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Remind me, Father, now, for I am weary of the world I see.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"636#2:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>Reveal what You would have me see instead.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"My true Identity is so secure, so lofty, sinless, glorious and great, wholly beneficent and free from guilt, that Heave